    <div class=3D"guide-content">
     =20


Before you start using Yarn, you'll first need to install it on your system=
. There are many different ways to install Yarn, but a single one is recomm=
ended and cross-platform:



<h2 id=3D"install-via-npm">Install via npm</h2>

<p>It is recommended to install Yarn through the <a href=3D"http://npmjs.or=
g/">npm package manager</a>, which comes bundled with <a href=3D"https://no=
dejs.org/">Node.js</a> when you install it on your system.</p>

<p>Once you have npm installed you can run the following both to <strong>in=
stall</strong> and <strong>upgrade</strong> Yarn:</p>

<div class=3D"language-sh highlighter-rouge"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre =
class=3D"rougeHighlight"><code>npm install <span class=3D"nt">--global</spa=
n> yarn
</code></pre></div></div>


<h2>Alternatives</h2>

